T*
(The active monetary schedule is implemented in monetary_policy.py.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Current schedule:) Tj
T*
(- kind: daily_fixed_point_decay_v1) Tj
T*
(- initial reward: 100.00000 ATHO/block) Tj
T*
(- initial daily issuance: 72,000.00000 ATHO/day) Tj
T*
(- total scheduled days: 109,575) Tj
T*
(- total scheduled blocks: 78,894,000) Tj
T*
(- max supply: 1,000,000,000.00000 ATHO) Tj
T*
(- corrected daily multiplier: 999_928_027_050_395_505 / 10^18) Tj
T*
(- last positive-subsidy height: 78,893,999) Tj
T*
(- first zero-subsidy height: 78,894,000) Tj
T*
(- tail reward: 0) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Consensus invariants:) Tj
T*
(- all value math is integer atoms) Tj
T*
(- total_emitted_atoms\(height\) <= 100,000,000,000,000) Tj
T*
(- block_subsidy_atoms\(78,894,000\) == 0) Tj
T*
(- supply stays pinned once the cap is reached) Tj
T*
(- coinbase payout must equal block subsidy + miner fee share) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Because fee burn and fee-pool routing are disabled, block-fee accounting is simple:) Tj
T*
(- fees_miner_atoms = total fees) Tj
T*
(- fees_burned_atoms = 0) Tj
T*
(- fees_pool_atoms = 0) Tj
T*
(- Reorg and State Safety) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Current replay and recovery focus is:) Tj
T*
(- public/private UTXO correctness) Tj
T*
(- private state apply/revert symmetry) Tj
T*
(- atomic tip advancement) Tj
T*
(- orphan/reorg recovery without legacy bond/stake state rebuilds) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(MAX_REORG_DEPTH_BLOCKS remains active. The legacy consensus finalization buffer is not part of) Tj
T*
(active BPoW policy anymore.) Tj
T*
(- Throughput Framing) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Measured tx-size behavior is still workload-dependent and documented separately in Tx.md. The) Tj
T*
(payment-only redesign did not change the principle that:) Tj
T*
(- public-heavy blocks are much denser than private-heavy blocks) Tj
T*
(- fee policy is vsize-based) Tj
T*
(- throughput estimates must be workload-specific, not one-number marketing claims) Tj
T*
